The paper focuses on utilizing web data for training convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and improving their performance on object recognition tasks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses using web search results and categories for training, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions using web data for object localization and detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
